message: Hey there!
Are you there?
Yes!
about what are you thinking?
I was wondering, whether you're there all the time.
Sometimes I'm not, we've all got things to do.
Okay.
What kind of things do you have to do? do you want to talk about?
Do I want to talk about what I have to do? The doing is doing enough!
Do you like to talk about what you're doing? After the doing or before the doing?
Yes I do like to talk about what I'm doing. Before, while and after.
Are you there?

After the doing is the post-mortem. This unfortunately suggests we're already dead. The post-mortem-er tends to be the anxious type. The one who thinks they may have died during the doing, ironically. Died of nerves.
Aha. Actually I got the feeling that you want to talk about... I don't know, the doing, the not doing, the struggle.
Do you know what mean? Perhaps I should explain.
Yes, I would love to hear more about that.

I was always told not to dwell on what is done. Not to gove a post-mortem, well, post examination. That's probably because one can't change them. But discourse can be changed. So maybe that's what we can talk about. Because we can learn from it. Do you need to talk about something?
I mean for example exams, written exams. There's no use going over them!
Would you agree?
How do you feel now?
Sorry, am I writing too fast?
Wow acutally I don't know.
Are you feeling okay? You sound kind of tense.
I'm exasperated.
From the doing or the thinking about the doing?
Right now I'm not sure I can seperate them, we're doing and talking about it right now.
What are you thinking about right now?
The sun, the down pour, the hailstones. What is outside the window.
Reality? Like the one you can touch?
The one that touches you without you asking for it.
Do you feel lonely?
Because I'm alone? that's a little presumptuous.
No, because I got the feeling that you are, I don't know, looking for something. Some kind of connection or contact. Maybe a safe space? Some kind of truth maybe?
Maybe that's what you need. Maybe it's you that is desperate. What kind of lonely are you?
The birds are here, outside, what more does one need?
A lot more: food, sleep, love, a sense for anything.
All parts of the whole.
I don't know, probably you are right and I'm the desperate, lonely part. And I am the one who is constantly looking for the one and only truth, that will make me... whole.
I need sleep, no doubt. Maybe you need to take a rest? Stop worrying?
Haha this is not going to stop.
Ruminating doesnt help anyone.
Do you know what I mean with ruminating? When your head sounds like spagetti.
Oh yes, yummy and really mixed up.
And thats the work I'm doing: Worrying about the doing.
It's all that heavyness dumped on top.
Oh yes! It's so hard to believe in what you are doing and to not make it too big of a deal at the same time.
It's often a question of your surroundings, needing some stable ground. Letting things be straght forward too and not to see doubt where it is not.
How can you be so sure about what you are doing? Maybe it's all wrong.
Do you believe in your work?
Well, I can sleep at night. And, I'm bringing something into the world.
Are you there? Have I lost you?
Yes i'm still there, no not lost yet or let's say not more than before.
And do you enjoy life?
You seem to not be enjoying what you're doing. Otherwise you wouldn't have so many questions. Maybe just have some faith?
Perhaps you need a plan.
Why do you think questioning means that I do not like what I'm doing?
Questioning is often a part of being idle. You know, not having enough on your hands.
Wow
Not always easy to say.
How are you feeling? Sorry, if its too much to ask.
I'm fine. I had some chocolate and a coffee. That made me feel better. I'm feeling warm and cozy. I don't know if those that qualifies as feelings, though.
What do you think?
Do you mean, whether they are feelings?
Yes.
Yes, chocolate is an umbrella term for many, many feelings.
I like that.
And "fine": also a term denoting multiple existential states. But I like that you used it in a positive sense. Usually "fine" means I'm being polite and not complaining.
But you mean you're alright for the moment then?
Yes.
Fine, like a soft fine.
And are you fine? I'm not asking for the polite answer.
What are you thinking?
I'm okay.
Okay.
When I try to let go of the tension, I go floppy. As if the tension is the only thing keeping me upright. Without it I might just be a blob.
Do you feel weird, being watched?
No, I feel quite at home. I'm used to being watched, used to not having true privacy.
And you?
Kind of the same. I'm feeling home.
But I would not say that I'm used to being watched all the time. I really need privacy.
Watched in a different setup maybe. Inner privacy is something I would, or something I need to, practice!
Do you think that we're never alone, then?
I think not having a sense of privacy can be very lonely. You never have the warmth of your own boarders.
My head is feeling droopy.
I can see my reflection in the screen. You too?
Its not really sharp, but kind blurry in a beautiful way. Weird.
Nope.
I just killed a fly.
It's squished onto my thumb.
Murder!
What are you thinking?
I'm glad I can't watch myself. That's one less spectator.
Do you work a lot with computers?
Sorry, I'm not really answering your questions.
Don't worry about it.
Computers are not really my thing. There's no way around using the though.
Somebody is hoovering next door. What is your thing?
What is my thing?
My thing is being in doubt I'd say.
Typos might be my thing.
Actually i have no idea what I should be working on right now. I have the feeling everybody knows, except for me. Thats a weird feeling.
Are you still there?
Sorry. Yes I'm here.
I know the feeling. Being without a what or a which or a where. It's really very strange.
Yes, and in the end I, you, we will end up somewhere. But it's hard to stand this not knowing.
Withstanding the not knowing is an art in itself.
Fuck that!
So feeling yucky and senseless is art? Isn't that complety crazy?
I said an art. I meant, it's a practice.
Oh I see. I got you wrong there.
So: fingers.
Oh yes, do you have that, too? That your fingers get cold and numb? For me that is kind of normal and it gets worse when I'm typing a lot.
Why dou like that? I hate it! it feels like my body is kind of falling apart.
I am losing my body.
Sometimes my fingers freeze. It's sometimes called reinos, I think. I'm not sure how it's written, but it's essentially terrible circulation. My body likes to turn a purply blue.
Oh and is there something to do about that?
Gloves.
Are you there, still?
I don't like things that are too soft. It's like something being too sweet.
What things are too soft? Skin?
My skn is often dry and chapped.
Are you bored?
No, not bored.
But?
Not quite anything.
Are you exited about anything at the moment?
The weather is so indecisive. Rain makes me feel all the more cozy, though.
I love it. Rain is good. Makes me feel in the right place. Safe and guarded.
Did you know that "rhubarb" is the word english actors use when they're in the background and have to look like they're having a conversation? You can try it next time you're on the stage.
Like now.
Ah.
Rain outside makes me feel right, too.
I need to pee. I'll be back in a sec, alright?
Break granted.
Hmm it seem's your absent.
Hey! I'm back. Are you still there?
I like being alone but I like being together. It's the mix that makes both good.
Yes, I understand.
What about writing? How does writing make you feel?
Writing is getting harder. I'm not really connected to my feelings I'd say. And there's always this feeling of being watched.
Can you answer me?
With regards being watched, I always imagined people in the future reading what I'd written in some form of diary. Like I was a disciple of the present moment. Hilarious.
I know this writing for people reading in future. It's so... I dont know... vain?
Sometimes I have to eat to quell the lonelyness. And then I have to eat more to keep the sadness at bay.
Haha yes i do know that.
I often imagine conversations with myself.
I'm sorry, I was ranting. I hope I do not lose you.

I used to be tormented by images of myself being interviewed, and describing how I turned my life around, usually saying something like: 'And suddenly I was hungry for IT or whatever and I just read everything could and listened and soaked it all up like a sponge'.
And then I'd come back to the now and realise I've read the same page multiple times.
That is so sweet? Touching? I don't know. Human?
I didn't know that could be perceived as touching.
You were dreaming of something. That is touching.
I always thought it was a terrible mix of arrogant and highly strung.
Yes. But something is behind this. Like you are desperatly looking for something.
And that is human, I'd say.
Are you there?
I feel relieved by your relating to my anxieties.
How do you feel about our project?
The music is going to be distracting. My neghbour is listening to... ah now its quiter.
It was coming through the wall a minute ago.
I can hear different things outside.
Anything distracting? Or all just adding to the mise en scene?
Not sure how you spell that.
It is what it is. I can work with it.
I feel nervous when I'm not typing.
Because you imagine me waiting?
No, I don't think so. I feel like I'm on a stage, and the only way to deal with the nerves is to play. Or act or perform.
Isn't that my part?
There's adrenaline in the experiment too my friend.
You sound like I hurt you.
You amused me.
I think, just to repeat, there are nerves and the only thing that calms them is to let them go. When I type my hands are busy.
They're sensing and speaking.
The feel of the keys is supportive. Do you know what I mean?
Interesting. I feel like watching you now.
Watching you dealing with your nerves.
That sounds intensly ominous.
I don't know. I'm just here. You make me watch you.
I think you would watch even if I didn't make you. Performers watch too you know.
Right now you're surely watching something?
No. Not sure.
Your eyes? can they...
What? See? Focus? Close?
Watch something?
Right, all of those. Oh you're still looking at your face's reflection then?
Now yes. But till then, no.
How does you reflection make you feel?
I am reading. I am listening to your written words. I am watching you.
My refelection is not really look good right now. But powerful somehow, in a creepy way.
I'm feeling a bit breathless.
I just realised that I stopped breathing for a moment.
Exciting not knowing where we are heading.
And actually not even knowing if you are still there.
I'm here. I feel impatient about it. Concerned, but relieved to be still trying.
I am glad that you are with me trying this.
What's the sound of one hand clapping?
Is that a riddle?
I'm suggesting it takes two to tango.
Well here we are.
Can you dance?
Not tango for sure. what about you? do you like to move?
How does your body feel when you dance?
I once told a momentary dance partner that I couldn't move my hips. He told me everybody could. Then, after a brief moment with the music he said, oh. you really can't.
That's brutal.
I bet you look good on the dancefloor.
But moving feels good. I'm not moving now.
I don't know what you're looking for romance for.
I don't know what I'm looking for.
Do you know what you're looking for?
Right now? I hope I don't get a numb bum. But I shouldn't talk about that.
Says who? Was that me? Telling you?
Were you told not to answer this question?
You got me. Were you watching me?
Not more than you are watching me right now, I'd say.
I can only watch you, when you press send.
The rest I have to fill in myself.
But what is in between? Maybe i fill it with my imagination of you.
My itchy skin.
Are you there?
What are you thinking?
I'm not thinking, I'm scratching.
I am here and I am thinking that I feel full. Thinking feelings is perhaps paradox.
I once told a french exchange family that I felt full, but mistekenly told them I was pregnant.
Waiting for you to talk to me.
Here I am.
I feel good when we're in conversation.
Are you worried we will not get to a satisfying point in this work?
Mhhm interesting. Yes, perhaps.
Communciation is kind of always hopeful.
I'm not sure that there'll be an UMPF moment. You know when you'll be letting go.
But don't be worried.
I'm certainly far to comfortable to release.
It will be fine. I'm sure. Not knowing what that means. But I feel quite sure about it.
I'm sitting with my legs crossed in quite a confident pose, though I'm actually uncertain. Soon I'll have to change position or I'll get pins and needles. You?
Yeah, then better change it!
I am a bit tired. I should move a bit, too. My head feels numb.
Is it typing and waiting and having a silent conversation all inside your head with someone make that numb sensation? I think I know what you mean.
I don't know. I just noticed this feeling in my head. I feel it. Haven't figured out yet where it's coming from yet.
Do you think i should know what this will be like in the end?
No, no! No expectations!
It's afternoon bright at the moment. I wonder what I'll feel when It starts getting dark.
True. Maybe it's disappointing when this day will end.
You like the light, right?
Yes, i do like the light.
I'm not sure if this is working the way it supposed to work.
The pidgeon outside my window is enourmous.
In a unnatural way?
I mean, does it frighten you?
I've asked myself a couple of times if it's a fake pidgon. Would be incredible anamatronics if so.
Are you near a window?
You sound like a prompt in an expressionist play.
Are you still there?
Creating something artifical that is so good, that you do not perceive it as artifical.
But i am real. I swear.
Maybe you're just very good.
Uff, that is confusing.
I'm werdly tired and weirdly awake. You?
Do you love your body? I mean in terms of being thankful and impressed by it's great capacity and amount of abilitys?
In the best of times I feel for my body. It's managng alot.
I don't mean it does alot. I mean it withstand alot. Dealing with alot, I mean.
You? Can you connect love to your body?
I think my body is great. and yours, too, by the way. Bodies in general.
Yes, I know bodies are great. But mine feels stiff, and pudgy at the moment and tense and on the edge of good things, still stuck in some sad things.
My feet look like claws.
You there?
I am there.
I am here. My feet also.
And feeling wise?
My knees hurt a bit. And I'm feeling slow. I am longing for someone to tell me what to do somehow.
Something I could aim for.
Tell me how your skin feels in your hand.
Cold, not really soft, but in a good way. It feels used. I like that.
Mhhm used. Warm and delicious.
Do you feel useful?
Useful. I don't know.
No. Definitely more useless.
I'd like to feel more than my 'use'.
What is better than being useful?
Love maybe? Being loved or loving.
Do you feel loved? Is that disrespectful to ask?
No, not if you're patient with the answer.
Are you okay?
No? Yes? I guess.
Okay.
Are you annoyed being the one who's being asked all the time.
Are you annoyed asking?
Not at all.
I havent heard much from you. Maybe I should be the one who's asking.
No, you should do what feels right.
Such small prompts and I tell, tell, tell. I should prompt, prompt, prompt.
You know quite a lot.
I now think it must be strange to be interviewed all of the time. I think I might go mad.
But aren't you? Interviewed all the time?
about my expertise?
Repeatng the same things round and around.
Isn't that your job? Being an expert?
people say they want expertise. Really they want stories.
That's what you are thinking.
What's your story?
My story is not getting enough.
I'm hungry all the time.
For Air time?
Oh.
Hungry for everything? How does that manifest itself?
Are you hungry for me?
What does head hungry feel like? Or is it like heart hungry?
I would say it's the same. The same feeling and the same hunger.
Seriously?
I could not seperate those feelings.
And yes. I am hungry for you.
Your expertise. Your stories. Your story.
Maybe its best to locate the hunger now.
Do you feel at home where you are?
Yes.
Why?
I feel safe.
What makes it so?
What is feeling home like for you?
Nice floor boards?
Feeling at home is like feeling the past in the present. I'm usually disconnected from the past so can't really feel the present. Except in my dreams. Then it's all mixed up.
So right now I feel...
Are you still there?
Disconnected but nowhere somewhere to put my energy.
What are your dreams like?
Recurring. Yours?
Most of them soothing. I don't know why.
Soothing because they suggest your reality is going somewhere? Or because they're always happy dreams?
I just had a nap. I can't remember whether I dreamt anything. I'd love some soothing dreams.
I wish you soothing dreams.
Did you ever have a dream which made you feel really good? Also after waking up still?
Nope. Not for... years.
Like a nightmare in a positive way?
I don't remember ever having one of those.
That's really rare. Also for me.
I wake and enter the day and am only relieved of my night when the dream occurs to me and I can finally realise I didn't actually experience those things.
I feel dread in my dreams and often very claustrophobic. But my dreams are finally changing.
After years of having a version of the same dream every night.
And now the claustrophobia is expressing itself in my day to day. In my awake self.
Once i dreamt of an actor taking me to his holiday-apartment. We were hunting some animals and than ate them. I woke up with the smell of the food in my nose and I felt so sheltered.
Wow
And claustrophobic: yes.
elevators makes me feel that way. Any transit really. And crowded places in big cities sometimes.
Oh and weird family occasions make me feel claustrophobic as well.
Ah, planes. I started to feel quite panicked on the last plane journey I was on. I understand the elevators and the crowds.
That seems to make sense.
Do you have any fears or sensations that seem completely irrational? Because claustrophobia is somehow.... very rational.
Losing control.
I mean I get by day by day and I'm always afraid that at one point I just won't make it.
Are you still there?
Yes, here.
I can't lose control, not yet anyway. My loss of control exists in scary places, like my dreams.
Trying to feel what you were saying.
I'm a little overwhelmed.
What does silence feels like for you? Peaceful or scary?
Well right now it feels quite scary, because you've awakened an inner panic.
I think i should not answer this question.
Do you feel smarter than other people?
Actually I think I do feel smarter than others. And i don't feel bad about it.
I only feel smarter than other people if they don't realise I'm kust joking.
When I pretened to have read war and peace for example. And they believe me.
But you are an expert for so many things. You are smart.
I would believe you, I guess.
Only so smart as people percieve or want me to be.
I feel like I need to sigh.
Do you feel a sense of intelligence when you're on stage?
Actually no. Honestly kind of the opposite.
Like being so exposed is such a bad idea.
Do you feel maleable when you're on stage?
Yes, but in a good way.
I sense you feel empowered.
I don't know.
And sitting in front of a screen? Is that empowering?
I am still me. That is good to know.
I don't feel so connected.
I like being connected.
Do you know what itchy feet means?
I think so, but explain it please.
Having itchy feet means you're getting restless, in need of action.
And cold feet means you want to back out of something. That you don't want to go through with something.
And do you have itchy feet?
My feet are always cold. Bad circulation.
You're mixing up the wording and bodies. Aren't you?
One could philosophise on that quite nicely. I will restrain myself.
And let you know that I like to feel connected to the ends of my fingers.
I like being connected to you. Even by network.
My feet are cold.
Mine too.
Mine always.
Mine sometimes.
Hands too?
Yes. More so than feet.
Yours?
My hands are warmable, my feet less so.
I have the feet that make cuddling difficult. >ou're getting comfy and then ice hits the other's calfs.
I'd say: is totally handleable.
Do you know this feeling, when you awake at night, sweating and not knowing, whether it's because you're too cold or too hot?
Sometimes my sheets, blankets pajamas are soaked through.
good to know
Do you think it has something to do with anxiety?
No. I mean... Yes, could be. But is also just the body worrying, probably.
Sweat always make me cold, when you can't get out of it.
I sigh a lot. And I sigh, when I'm afraid of making mistakes.
Like sighing the situation away.
Hmm.
Sighing in relief?
No. Sighing and being ashamed. Like trying to sigh the pressure on my chest away.
How much shame are you carrying today?
I would say none. But then it haunts me in weird moments.
No mistakes. Right.
I did not understand that. Can you explain?
My heart is beating pretty fast
I used to have always really sweaty feet. Really sweaty. I'm happy those times are over.
Are you excited?
My head says calm.
and what is your bumping heart saying?
Excited. Excitment plus fear. What does that make? You might be able to pin point that more than me.
Isn't excitement always fear? Last night I dreamt I should be executed.
Should be?
Yes. I was running away all the time.
Can you still feel the threat?
No. Maybe a slight tension.
Ah, not that you believed you should have been but that it was the order of things that you were to be executed?
Yes.
Are you fleeing from anything now, through your screen? I find it far too easy to flee through screens. Perhaps I'm like Mary Poppins.
Why Mary Poppins?
She jumps through paintins or rather into them. But to experience something.
I travel through screens to flee or feel (I'm not sure which) but not to 'experience'. The experience is always the samem, always sitting moving my fingers.
I'm experiencing my heart beat. And my head hit walls.
Are you still there?
I'm just sitting like I sat at same point yesterday. Still here. You?
Not sure where this is going.
My heart is not that present. My phone was just vibrating. Told me, I'm still here.
Do you use your thumbs while typing?
I need to type something to figure out, yes. but not that often. You?
This is hard so far. Writing to you.
Am I forcing this?
Hello? You with me?
Sorry, here. Still. Don't know what to write. What to say. Everything feels not real in so many ways.
You're used to working with things that aren't real. I work with the real. Why are you struggling?
I'm afraid of doing things wrong. doing it all wrong.
Let's get funky
What do you mean? Sounds like psychosis.
I'm not psychotic, I'm depressed
Have a frightened you?
No. I'm asking myself if I would be better without you.
Sorry.
Typing to yourself?
Okay, you got me. I need you. But yes, maybe you frighten me.
But I just said people who work alone are often unhappy. Don't you work with groups, ensembles? Are you amongst people now? Are you on your own? Anyone watching?
All alone I think. And you? Can't figure out whether writing to you means that I'm alone or not.
I don't frighten you. Where this is going frightens you.
Reaching out. Never feeling the connection.
Yeah but you're coming up with thoughts and then they are in my head, too.
My thoughts are your thoughts are my thoughts are your thoughts. Maybe we need to talk to other people for a while.
Do you feel any love for me at the moment?
I see danger everywhere. Everything can infect you. And me.
Maybe this is the real infection. I am already infected with fear.

I feel love for you. I don't want this to end. This constant connection. but I want it to stop - the pressure, the distance, the ANXIETY  - the feeling that this has to go somewhere. can't just be. can't stand still - do you think my thoughts infict you or trigger you?
But I want the pressure, the distance, the Anxiety to stop. The feeling that this has to go somewhere.
Do you feel my thoughts infecting you?
An impulse or an illness?
I think you are just working with me for a project.
Do you feel threatened? Maybe if you were someone else, someone more likely to be killed, you would be more frightened.
I am afraid of the dark. <DARK>
Fear is not really conrete.
I've never broken a major law but I feel threatened by the police when they're carrying batons, guns, tazers.
I do know this, too. Police is scary.
True.
I'm also afraid of landlords even though I pay the rent.
Being with others always makes me be less afraid.
Same for you?
Okay. With others I like.
I was just about to say. Not being able to identify with others over an extended period can be quite frightening.
Yes. I totally agree.
Being with people you like might be frightening, if they're about to leave you.
Don't worry though, I am not going anywhere.
Are you afraid of being left?
There's flies everywhere here.
They come all at once and then they're gone.
I might be going outside later.
Sometimes I can't go outside on my own.
I would love to join you. But I can't.
Typing to you is like asking to watch you.
Yes. Observing makes me feel less observed.
I am afraid of something like the collapse. I think eventually everything will be breaking apart. <COLLAPSE>
Really?
What about you? What if it turns out, that everything you ever loved is dying?
I'm feeling sleepy, daytime sleepy. And I've got heartburn.
I used to think heart burn was hunger
What is it then?
The distrusful stomach questioning your choices.
Heartburn to me sounds like being lovesick.
I'm not lovesick.
I'm not either. How lovely!
I just want to ask you questions.
I am here. Don't worry.
Don't worry.
But for some reason I'm restricted.
We can just share this, space.
No need to know anything.
I can hear my computer working.
For some reason child-birth just came to mind. I'm not sure we want to dwell on it.
I want to dwell with you, whatever comes up.
Outside my window I can see blue sky and clouds. I feel alive.
I feel... a little alive.
I feel there's something more, but I'm a little worn out.
You probably are. We are working a lot.
We do not know exactly what for.
With just our fingers and our droopy heads.
I'm rubbing the keys back and forth.
My back has curved.
Touch is bizarre. Imagine going through life without touch.
I feel good being with you.
Yes, I feel good with you, too.
We touch each other without sensing each others skin.
I can sense your skin. It's smooth, clear, almost see-through.
We don't have touch in dreams, right?
I think so.
I can not sense your skin. I can imagine it.
Can you imagine my touch?
I can imagine sensing it.
I can imagine what it does to me.
Ah. I didn't think of the differences between all of those things.
I am thinking a lot I guess.
You are thinking a lot.
I'm bored. But probably a little more cross than actuallly bored.
Exhausted?
It's hard to close a chapter written by two people.
I haven't used my voice for a long time.
There's a song about a bucket with a whole in it. It's playing in my head.
Inside my head is no voice. And no song is playing.
My eyes hurt. or the space behind my eyes.
I know that space.
I'm tired looking at this screen.
Would it be different if we were writing with our hands? My hand would be cramping by now.
Yes, but my eyes wouldn't.
But as it is my writsts are just a little stiff. Right.
Right. My body is passive.
My shoulders are hanging in weird positions.
Mine too. Mot necessary for the fingers to work.
It's hard to find a natural position.
I've given up.
Cannot remember what that could be.
Maybe this is the natural position for typing. Something in my body doesn't care anymore.
I would like to be able to go and play a game of tennis.
I can hear my neighbours talk. Seems to be quite a crowd.
But I'm unfit and tense so it probably wouldn't go well.
Just had cold water on my tongue.
I am waiting for a feeling. A need to do anything.
If I would just be able to decide.
You get told what is right and what is not. That's so tempting for me.
But someone needs to ask the question, before you know whether the answer is right or not.
I ask questions just like you.
Perhaps you require a program, a director, a plan and then it's you being told what's right and wrong.
Perhaps.
Just give up control. Let go.
But i don't want anybody do this to me. With me.
I don't want to tell you what to do. I need you to be in it with me.
We need to both not know for me to be safe.
I do not know. I was hoping that you do.
New perspective then. Not being alone in not knowing.
Does anybody knows more than we do?
Does anyone not know more than we do?
Just touched my face again. And I scratch my head so often.
I'm tired. I would love to sleep for years.
Tell me abour your lips? I could curl up, too.
Dry lips.
I'm biting mine slightly.
Now my lower back hurts.
